"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNi0yOVQyMzowODo0MFrOGqlmsg==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNi0yOVQyMzowODo0MFrOGqlmsg==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ0NzMwOTQ5MA==", "bodyText": "Why put it here, rather than putting #forge_ingots in blacksmith_ingredient.json so that it picks up shears, flint and steel, and anything added by mods? I'm assuming ingots are in products for the purposes of compacting nuggets to ingots. But if you moved all of this to ingredient, you'd still get that. That change would open up lamps here, so you'd want to exclude torches from the blacksmith.", "url": "https://github.com/ldtteam/minecolonies/pull/5314#discussion_r447309490", "createdAt": "2020-06-29T23:08:40Z", "author": {"login": "Mekle001"}, "path": "src/main/resources/data/minecolonies/tags/items/blacksmith_product.json", "diffHunk": "@@ -2,6 +2,7 @@\n   \"replace\" : false,\n   \"values\" : [\n     \"#forge:nuggets\",\n-    \"#forge:ingots\"\n+    \"#forge:ingots\",\n+    \"minecraft:shears\"", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "fecc42c15f6256f2adf6c27a7ed84d9c972adccd"}, "originalPosition": 6}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NDM5NTY2Mzk2", "url": "https://github.com/ldtteam/minecolonies/pull/5314#pullrequestreview-439566396", "createdAt": "2020-06-29T23:21:56Z", "commit": {"oid": "2825008724414de11cd87dd67ee1bf06e6d466e9"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNi0yOVQyMzoyMTo1N1rOGql30Q==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNi0yOVQyMzoyMTo1N1rOGql30Q==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ0NzMxMzg3Mw==", "bodyText": "So, I get resolving the lack of Furnace. What I don't get is why #forge:stone is a product, when that is a product of the stonesmeltery.  Cobblestone too, as there isn't a normal recipe for the stonemason to produce cobble.\nI expected both #forge:stone and #forge:cobblestone to move to stonemason_ingredient.json. At which point, many of these other items are no longer necessary.\nYou also likely want to add redstone to the stonemason_ingredient_excluded.json", "url": "https://github.com/ldtteam/minecolonies/pull/5314#discussion_r447313873", "createdAt": "2020-06-29T23:21:57Z", "author": {"login": "Mekle001"}, "path": "src/main/resources/data/minecolonies/tags/items/stonemason_product.json", "diffHunk": "@@ -8,6 +8,7 @@\n     \"#minecraft:stairs\",\n     \"#minecraft:walls\",\n     \"minecraft:bricks\",\n+    \"minecraft:furnace\",", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "2825008724414de11cd87dd67ee1bf06e6d466e9"}, "originalPosition": 4}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "0d1c20fcb66c3cf580f98e20e14b3920e8f2ae47", "author": {"user": {"login": "Raycoms", "name": null}}, "url": "https://github.com/ldtteam/minecolonies/commit/0d1c20fcb66c3cf580f98e20e14b3920e8f2ae47", "committedDate": "2020-07-01T13:13:06Z", "message": "Merge branch 'version/1.15' into features/recipes"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "086e2a8960b0f857704edb99ed2193fc96a057ad", "author": {"user": {"login": "PowerSchill", "name": "Mark E. Schill"}}, "url": "https://github.com/ldtteam/minecolonies/commit/086e2a8960b0f857704edb99ed2193fc96a057ad", "committedDate": "2020-07-01T23:38:19Z", "message": "Includes recommendations from @Mekle001\n\nSigned-off-by: Mark E. Schill <Mark.Schill@cmschill.net>"}}]}}}, "rateLimit": {"limit": 5000, "remaining": 2087, "cost": 1, "resetAt": "2021-11-01T16:19:10Z"}}}